Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} and slice into 1cm rounds. Pop
the aubergine slices onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer. Roast the
aubergine until golden brown and soft, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve,
peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or
use a #garlic press{}). Drain the @mozzarella{1} and pull it apart into small pieces.

When the water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and cook until tender,
~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan and
drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir every couple
of minutes. Add the @tomato puree{30%g} and garlic to the pan, stir together and
cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1},
@water{100%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat to medium and
simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Taste the sauce and add @salt{}, @pepper{} and a @sugar{pinch} if necessary. Add the
cooked pasta to the sauce along with half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}
and stir to combine. Put half the pasta in an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer the cooked
aubergine slices on top of the pasta and finish with the remaining pasta on top. Put
the mozzarella on top, followed by the remaining hard Italian style cheese. Switch
your #oven to grill setting on high heat - grill the pasta until the cheese is golden
and bubbly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Put the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a medium #bowl{} and add the @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once the pasta bake is cooked, serve in large
#bowls{}. Add the @wild rocket{40%g} and @croutons{1} to the dressing and toss to
coat. Serve the pasta with the rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!